<TITLE> Khaleda, sons to be freed soon on parole </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 19 (bdnews24.com)  Former prime minister Khaleda Zia will soon be freed on parole Saturday for several hours to attend the funeral of her mother Toyeba Majumdar, the home ministry said in a statement. Khaleda's two sons Tarique Rahman and Arafat Rahman Coco will also be released on parole. A helicopter will carry the body of Toyeba to Dhaka from Dinajpur. DMP commissioner Naim Ahmed told bdnews24.com that the police put in place an adequate security arrangement for Khaleda and her two sons. According to an official order, Khaleda was scheduled to stay on parole from 11am to 5pm. But Khaleda's lawyer advocate Mahbubuddin Khokon complained that the government was delaying the release of Khaleda. Toyeba's son Shamim Eskanderaccompanied by his wifearrived in Dinajpur Saturday morning to take the body to Dhaka. Khaleda's lawyer Barrister Ahmed Azam Khan had earlier told bdnews24.com that the body of Toyeba would be flown to Dhaka Cantonment. The body will then be taken to Azad Mosque in Gulshan for a namaz-e-janaza after Asr prayers. The body will be flown back to Dinajpur town for burial. Toyeba died of heart attack at a Dinajpur hospital Friday, aged 87. bdnew
